The paper proposes an unsupervised algorithm for salient object detection using game theory and multiple cues. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as the primary category. The algorithm also involves deep features and iterative random walk, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on multiple datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
